oblox’s game pass and developer product system. If the person you want to donate to has a game on Roblox, they can create a game pass or developer product that represents the “donation” amount.\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Step 1:<\/strong> Ask the recipient if they have a Roblox game where they can set up a game pass or developer product.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Step 2:<\/strong> They create a game pass priced at the desired Robux donation amount.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> You purchase the game pass, effectively transferring Robux to them minus Roblox’s platform fee.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\nThis method is widely used because it’s official and secure. However, keep in mind Roblox takes a percentage of the transaction (usually 30%), so the recipient won’t receive the full amount.\n\n<h3>2. Trading Limited Items<\/h3>\n\nAnother indirect way to donate Robux is through trading limited items. Limited items are special avatar accessories or collectibles that can be bought and sold for Robux in the Roblox marketplace.\n\n<ul>\n  <li>You can buy a limited item and then trade it with the user you want to donate to.<\/li>\n  <li>They can later sell that item on the marketplace to receive Robux.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\nThis method requires both users to have Roblox Premium subscriptions, as trading is only available to premium members. It’s a bit more complicated but can be a fun way to share Robux while also giving cool collectibles.\n\n<h3>3. Creating and Selling Items in a Group<\/h3>\n\nIf you and the donation recipient belong to the same Roblox group, you can collaborate to create virtual items or game passes that generate Robux. When you sell these items, the Robux earned can be distributed among group members.\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Group owners control the distribution of Robux from group sales.<\/li>\n  <li>This method requires some setup but can be an excellent way to support creators within a community.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h2>What You Should Know About Roblox’s Robux Transfer Policies